news.title: Consumer forum directs Cholamandalam Investment to return house documents to owner
news.para: Terming the action of Cholamandalam Investment and Finance Company for refusing to extend the benefit of insurance to S Naga Malliswari of Malkajgiri as 'cheating' and also an 'unfair trade practice,' the forum asked the company to pay a compensation of 1 lakh and legal costs of 5,000 to her.

news.title: Guwahati civic body to outsource property tax collection job
news.para: This was revealed by urban affairs minister Ashok Singhal on Monday. He said about 40% of around 3 lakh households in the city do not pay taxes.

news.title: Goa: TCP department appoints six professionals to issue clearances for low-risk buildings
news.para: The empanelled architects and engineers are now waiting for the department to prepare and notify the forms which will be used to issue third-party approvals.

news.title: Punjab government working on ways to deal with building violations
news.para: ​Punjab local bodies minister Inderbir Singh Nijjar said OTS made more sense for compoundable violations, but in the majority of cases, people had made drastic changes in approved building plans and it was not possible to regularise them.

news.title: Uttarakhand HC says tenants can vote in RWA elections
news.para: The HC observed that the residents pay for the services and therefore they also have the right to elect RWA members of their choice. Till now, only the owner of the flat or house was allowed to cast a vote in the RWA elections, not the tenants.

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad civic body to install construction & demolition waste plant
news.para: In order to find a solution to the problems posed by construction and demolition (C&D) waste, the civil work to setup of the C&D waste recycling plant in Shivalli is almost over.

news.title: Indore civic body lens on 20,000 properties for lapses in construction
news.para: This comes after IMC’s revenue department found additional construction in around 45,00 properties with construction size of above 5000 sq ft and issued notices to their respective owners for difference of the property tax from the date of registration.

news.title: Karnataka CM orders inquiry into encroachment of lakes in Bengaluru
news.para: Revenue Minister R Ashoka said out of 42 lakes that ceased to exist in Bengaluru so far, 28 have been “swallowed” by Bangalore Development Authority (BDA), five by Bruhat Bengaluru Mahanagara Palike (BBMP), one is BDA authorised, and seven by encroachers.

news.title: Maharashtra government cancels all GRs related to redevelopment of Mhada buildings
news.para: All the GRs pertained to the requirement of a prior no-objection certificate from the state government for carrying out redevelopment.

news.title: OYO reports revenue at Rs 1,459 crore in April-June 2022
news.para: For FY22, revenue from contract with customers was at Rs 4,781.4 crore. In FY21 it was at Rs 3,961.65 crore; Rs 13,168.15 crore in FY20 and Rs 6,329.74 crore in FY19, it added.

news.title: Protected Aravali land abuzz with construction, roads to borewells
news.para: This flurry of construction is underway in at least six sites at the Aravali Retreat in Raisina Hills, even though the land is protected under Section 4 of the Punjab Land Preservation Act (PLPA) as ‘gair mumkin pahar (uncultivable hill)’.

news.title: Gurugram civic body to file new plan for infrastructure in colonies by Sept 30
news.para: The tentative estimates for infrastructure augmentation were around Rs 8.5 crore for Sushant Lok 2, Rs 10 crore for Sushant Lok 3, Rs 8.5 crore for Ardee City and Rs 14 crore for Malibu Towne. However, these estimates will be revised.

news.title: MSEDCL starts cutting supply to Lavasa project over dues
news.para: An order from the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal dated September 2 had allowed the MSEDCL to terminate or suspend supply for non-payment of dues.

news.title: HDFC Capital raises over Rs 500 crore in first close of proptech fund
news.para: Through its initiative, HDFC Affordable Real Estate and Technology Program (HeART), it is looking to provide a platform to real estate technology companies with innovative products that would create competences and lower costs in each phase of the development cycle of a real estate project.

news.title: CBI files charge sheet against Rana Kapoor, Gautam Thapar in bank fraud case
news.para: In its charge sheet filed before the special CBI court in Mumbai, the probe agency has also named Thapar and Oyster Buildwell Pvt Ltd (OBPL) in the scam.
